3ï¸âƒ£ Anchors (ALWAYS asked)

| Symbol | Meaning                           |
| ------ | --------------------------------- |
| `^`    | Start of line                     |
| `$`    | End of line                       |
| `\A`   | Start of string (Rails preferred) |
| `\z`   | End of string                     |

Interview tip â­

ğŸ‘‰ Rails prefers \A and \z, not ^ and $.

/\Aabc\z/   # EXACT match

4ï¸âƒ£ Character classes (core concept)
Literal characters
/cat/


Matches: cat inside any string

Character sets [ ]
/[abc]/


Matches: a OR b OR c

/[a-z]/


Matches: lowercase letters

Negated set [^ ]
/[^a-z]/


Matches: anything NOT aâ€“z

5ï¸âƒ£ Shorthand classes (must know)

| Regex | Meaning                      |
| ----- | ---------------------------- |
| `\d`  | Digit (0â€“9)                  |
| `\w`  | Word (aâ€“z, Aâ€“Z, 0â€“9, _)      |
| `\s`  | Whitespace                   |
| `.`   | Any character except newline |

6ï¸âƒ£ Quantifiers (VERY commonly asked)

| Symbol  | Meaning         |
| ------- | --------------- |
| `+`     | One or more     |
| `*`     | Zero or more    |
| `?`     | Zero or one     |
| `{n}`   | Exactly n       |
| `{n,}`  | At least n      |
| `{n,m}` | Between n and m |

Example
/\d+/      # one or more digits
/\d{10}/   # exactly 10 digits

7ï¸âƒ£ Grouping & alternation
Grouping ( )
/(abc)+/


Matches:

abc

abcabc

OR operator |
/(cat|dog)/


Matches:

cat

dog

